definitions.definition: A white crystalline hydrocarbon manufactured from coal tar ; used in mothballs .
An aromatic bicyclic hydrocarbon, C 10 H 8 ; an acene containing two fused benzene rings .

main_definition: A white crystalline hydrocarbon manufactured from coal tar ; used in mothballs .
secondary_definitions: ( organic chemistry ) An aromatic bicyclic hydrocarbon, C 10 H 8 ; an acene containing two fused benzene rings .
